# {{ .name }}

.NET transactional integration job. Polls JSON orders from a local inbound folder,
publishes them onto an in-memory Dapr pub/sub topic, processes each one through a
VETER pipeline, and writes the transformed result to a local outbound folder.

## Run

Prepare the working folders and drop the bundled sample order into the inbound folder:

```bash
mkdir -p /tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/inbound /tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/outbound
cp local/sample-data/sample-order.json /tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/inbound/
```

Then run the job:

```bash
dapr run \
  --app-id {{ .appId }} \
  --dapr-http-port 3500 \
  --resources-path ./local/dapr-components \
  -- dotnet run --project ./src
```

The runner picks up the file, publishes it via in-memory pub/sub to topic `orders`,
runs the send pipeline, writes the transformed JSON to
`/tmp/{{ .name | kebabcase }}/outbound/<orderId>.json`, and deletes the source file.

## Pipeline

**Receive** (per source file):

1. `Receiver` reads bytes from the inbound binding.
2. `Enqueuer` publishes the payload to `pubsub` / `orders`.
3. `Completer` deletes the source file.

**Send** (per pub/sub delivery):

1. `Deserializer` parses the JSON into `In`.
2. `Extractor` pass-through.
3. `Validator` enforces required fields and basic business rules.
4. `Transformer` maps `In` → `Out` and sums the line totals.
5. `Serializer` serializes back to JSON.
6. `Sender` writes the JSON to the outbound binding using `<orderId>.json`.
